The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, January 11, 2004 				 Two French scribes get jail terms
																								Karachi, Jan. 10 (Agencies): A Pakistani court has sentenced two French journalists to six months in prison and fined them about $1,700 each after they pleaded guilty to visiting a city near the Afghan border without permission.																								Marc Epstein and Jean-Paul Guilloteau, both from the French weekly LExpress, were arrested on December 17 after visiting the southwestern city of Quetta, the capital of Baluchistan province. They accepted that they are pleading guilty without any pressure, after which the court awarded six month of rigorous imprisonment and a fine of 100,000 rupees each, said government lawyer, Mehmood Alam Rizvi.The scribes were working on a documentary about the Taliban. 
